\pard\f0\fs28 Sect. ADONIS. Annuals. Petals 8 or fewer, usually red, though often yellow when dried. Anthers blackish-purple.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28 All species occur as weeds of cultivation or in similar open habitats; although not strictly calcicole, they are found mainly on base-rich soils.
\par 

