\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. A. annua }L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 547 (1753) ({\i A. autumnalis} L.). Stems 10-70 cm. Leaves 3-pinnate, the segments linear, mucronate. Flowers 15-25 mm in diameter. Sepals ovate, patent. Petals 5-8, suberect, concave, oblong, somewhat longer than the sepals, bright scarlet, with a dark basal spot. Inner margin of achene nearly straight, the outer curved; beak short, straight, green throughout.{\i  Cultivated land. S. Europe, extending northwards to N. France; sometimes naturalized and often a casual elsewhere.} Al †Be Bl Bu Co Cr Ga Gr He Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu [Br].
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b annua} (incl.{\i  A. baetica} Cosson): Sepals glabrous. Achenes 4·5-5·5(-6) mm.{\i  Almost throughout the range of the species}.
\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b cupaniana} (Guss.) C. Steinb.,{\i  Webbia }{\b 25}: 324 (1971): Sepals hairy. Achenes 3-4·5 mm.{\i  S. Europe}.
